trans-unit.source: Iterates over combinations. A _combination_ of length n is a subsequence of the original array, with the elements taken in order. Thus, Array("x", "y") and Array("y", "y") are both length-2 combinations of Array("x", "y", "y"), but Array("y", "x") is not. If there is more than one way to generate the same subsequence, only one will be returned.

Iterators are data structures that allow to iterate over a sequence of elements. They have a hasNext method for checking if there is a next element available, and a next method which returns the next element and advances the iterator.
